class WeatherSimulator {
    private boolean sunny = true;

    public void setWeather(boolean isSunny) {
        sunny = isSunny;
    }

    public boolean isRainy() {
        return !sunny;
    }

    public void causeRain(boolean intervention) {
        if (intervention) {
            sunny = false;
        }
    }

    public void predictSunshineEffect(boolean causeAssert) {
        if (causeAssert) {
            sunny = true;
        }
        System.out.println("If it's sunny: " + sunny);
    }
}",

Judging only from observing that it is not rainy, can we conclude 'sunny' was set to true?
